    title: "The Great Filter Theory: The Most Disturbing Idea In Science",
    excerpt: "Economist Robin Hanson proposed an idea in 1998 that keeps physicists, philosophers, and anyone who thinks seriously about it awake at night. If it's correct, our future may be very short.",
    category: "alien-theories",
